As an American I was interested in trying the Kangaroo Steak.  My wife and I ordered the sampler entree to start and everything was fresh, hot, and delicious.  On the sampler plate the calamari was excellent as were the mushrooms and rice balls.  The bruschetta tomatoes and onions were fresh and delicious.

I eat a lot of wild American game (elk, venison, and antelope).  I loved the texture of the Kangaroo.  It was milder than I was expecting yet offered a distinctive dining option with a perfect temperature (medium rare with a perfect amount of char on the meat).  The Kangaroo was very tender, and the sauce with capers was an excellent combo with the garlic mashed potatoes.

I have had Italian food around the world, but if you dine here I would recommend the same meal (sampler plate and Kangaroo).  My wife and I enjoyed the food quality, helpful staff, and warm evening.

The only small feedback was the wine was served warmer than I am accustomed to (normally 15-17 degrees or so) at American restaurants.

[{'name': 'places/ChIJ_xrZZEtd1moRxb9el7EM1TA/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTUNBbmREeDRRRRAB', 'relativePublishTimeDescription': 'a month ago', 'rating': 4, 'text': {'text': "My review is actually only for the restaurant, however I can say that I visited my parents room and it was clean, huge and looked great.

The deal-breaker was the rushed service. Server tried to clear my bowl when I was just taking a break, with 1/3 still left!

Pros:
+ Fair pricing, no hidden fees
+ No weekend surcharge
+ Traditional pickled garlic
+ Clean venue

- Inauthentic pho

With three levels, it offers games of all kinds and so many spaces to play them. You can hire almost any game from the bar and play with friends or solo, which is such a fun experience.

We wandered around and eventually decided to play a board game called Psycho Killer, which was fantastic. The pixelated fire added a surprisingly cozy touch to the large space, and there were plenty of similar little nooks throughout. We got some drinks, which were nice and reasonably priced, and the service was excellent. Even at 12am the place still had a lively vibe, with dedicated gamers streaming or playing.

The space is so well-designed and thoughtfully themed, it’s truly a gamer’s paradise. If you’re a game lover, don’t miss this place! You can even try your hand at arcade games and go for one of the many prizes. Shorelist restaurant is getting smashed daily by hundreds. If not possibly thousands of people per day. To notice the tiny things shouldn't take away from a great meal.
